node.text: Topped with a colorful mix of tropical fruit, toasted nuts, and seeds, these open-faced chocolate disks from chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) can be made ahead and served right from the fridge. Plus, they come together with the help of none other than your microwave! Find out how to make Tropical Mendiants by visiting this link https://bit.ly/2VLcZMq or tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.text: The secret to these flavor-packed, plant-based nachos from @chefmamacass2 are two different kinds of lentils: black and red. Crispy pita chips are smothered with an the irresistable feta queso, layers of pepper-tinged lentil chili, rose harissa-spiked pickled cabbage, and dollops of yogurt. It's definitely a dish worth sharing. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.title: FWCooks | Loaded Pita Nachos with Lentil Chili and Feta Queso

Find out how to add some 'cue to your greens through the link in bio.

node.text: As Chef Paola Velez (@smallorchids) says “chocolate is life” and these Tropical Mendiants are life-changing. Piped into rounds, the chocolates are topped with a colorful mix of tropical fruit, toasted nuts, and seeds that look as good as they taste. Watch the full episode on IGTV! #PastriesWithPaola

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food & Wine on August 14, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Talk about summer on a plate! This Tomato-and-Peach Salad with Crisp Tofu recipe features sweet, salty, spicy, and tangy flavors from a zippy ginger-lime dressing. Everything gets a touch of heat from serrano peppers and pan-seared tofu. Tap the link in bio for the recipe! 🥗: @hughacheson 📸: @conpoulos_photographer

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food & Wine on August 14, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: The key to this Brothy Braised Chicken Thighs with Fennel and Pernod recipe is the slow-rendered fat. Not only does it make for a stunning piece of poultry, it also seeps into the veggies, melting them to an irresistibly silky texture that might just outshine the main. Tap the link in bio for everything you need to make this one-pot wonder! 🍗: @coluhenry 📸: @antonisachilleos

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food & Wine on August 13, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: This rich, chocolatey, and filling Double Chunk Brownies recipe from Lee Lee Reid of @nathanielreidbakery is a truly comforting dessert. Everything comes together in three steps to create the ideal brownie balance of a cakey *and* fudgy texture. Tap the link in bio to start baking! 📸: @gregdupree

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food & Wine on August 13, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: It’s National Filet Mignon Day, so what better way to celebrate than with a classic Steak Diane recipe. This style calls for sautéing thinly sliced or pounded filet mignon in butter and then flambéing and basting it in a rich Cognac sauce. Tap the link in bio to celebrate with steak tonight! 🥩: @emeril 📸: @dmalosh

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food & Wine on August 13, 2021. May be an image of gelato and icecream.

node.text:
The surprising secret to this creamy Vegan Vanilla Bean Ice Cream—pea milk—has the right balance of unsaturated fat, protein and a mild flavor. Cane sugar, vanilla extract and vanilla bean seeds all help enrich this creamy dessert. Tap the link in bio for this sweet treat! 
🍦: @paigegrandjean 📸: @protazio

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food & Wine on August 12, 2021. May be an image of chow mein and indoor.

node.text:
No chopping or slicing is required for this Thin Spaghetti with Tomatoes, Kalamata Olives, Feta, and Mint recipe. Whip up this one-pot wonder when you're short on time but craving a satisfying meal with very little effort. Tap the link in bio for the recipe! 
🍝: @justinchapple 📸: @gregdupree

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food & Wine on August 12, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text:
Tender summer squash melts into the batter of this Chocolate Zucchini Bread with Pepitas. A bit of ground cinnamon spices up the rich, chocolatey, and moist quick bread. Tap the link in our bio to get your bake on. 
🍽️: @paigegrandjean 📸: @jencausey

node.text: Need a dessert that’s easy to make and pleases a crowd? Chef Paola Velez’ (@smallorchids) Tropical Mendiants will definitely do the trick. The colorful and delicious chocolate disks can be made ahead, be served right from the fridge, and call for just a microwave instead of a stovetop. Try the latest #PastriesWithPaola creation through the link in bio! 📸: @reallyfarrah

node.text: On this episode of Chefs At Home, @dan_churchill of @charleyst combines a melange of mushrooms, broccoli, tofu, and wine to create a hearty filling for his Aussie Meat(less) Pie in an ode to his home country, @australia. The buttery and tender handrolled crust is the golden crown on this plant-powered gem. Tap the link in bio to watch the full episode on YouTube! #Sponsored

node.text:
Both beautiful and economical, this Tomatoes with Herbs and Almond Vinaigrette recipe is a keeper. Onion and jalapeno join toasted almonds for a bit of crunch while richly flavored oil makes a nice, tangy dressing for this total summer showstopper. 
🍽️: @dan_kluger 📸: @johnkernick
